# Class: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/REHABO_0010002> (medical device)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/REHABO_0010002> "An object manufactured with a function either (1) to diagnose, cure, mitigate, treat, or prevent disease or (2) to alter physically (i.e., not chemically) the structure or functioning of some part of the body of an organism."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/REHABO_0010002> "It is an object and not a material entity, because when the FDA approves certain reagents as medical devices, it is approving container+solution, which is an object per BFO. Note that such reagents are for use, for example, in the laboratory, and are not ingested (those would be drug products per the FDA)."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000117> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/REHABO_0010002> "Manoj Purohit"@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000233> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/REHABO_0010002> <https://github.com/mcwdsi/rehabo/issues/63>)
